Flights Data Explanation¶

by Ahmed Mokhtar¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

Airline on-time performance¶

This dataset was about all flights in the US, and this data was recorded between (Jan 2017) and (June 2020), and it contains the number of flights on different air-line carriers such as (Delta Air Lines Inc., Endeavor Air Inc., ..., etc. ), and from which airport was the takeoff.

It shows the total delay time in minutes for all flights, and the delay time went for different reasons.

The data also has the number of canceled flights and why they canceled

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

This data is about flights between 2017-2020, It has some columns to represent the flight date in a month, others to represent the city and airport name and the carrier company, then the rest columns represnt the number of flights, and the delayed or cancelled flights

I divieded the original dataframe into four dataframes by year, to compare between them

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The number of flights, the total delay, arr_diverted, and the city.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your featurce(s) of interest?¶

we need to gather city from airport, (carrier_delay, weather_delay, nas_delay, security_delay, and late_aircraft_delay) will give us better understand to arr_delay, and (carrier_ct, weather_ct, nas_ct, security_ct, late_aircraft_ct) will give us better understand to arr_cancelled.

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. How did the feature(s) of interest vary with other features in the dataset?¶

We can see from the previous scatter plots that there are highly positive correlations between the total fight delay and other delay reasons, but the security delay doesn't cause a huge effect, as it has a low correlation with the flight delay

We can see from the violin plot that G4 carrier has the lowest mean, and also it has the largest width, which means that most data fall in the low range, and the data is pretty high, and on the other hand WN has the highest mean and very thin width, and this mean it has low flights, So we can consider that WN has low flight numbers and high delay time due to carrier, and the opposite in G4 carrier, So WN must take care about this delay, this could be a reason to have low flight number.

Did you observe any interesting relationships between the other features (not the main feature(s) of interest)?¶

We can see that the effect of the coronavirus on flight number on the second quarter in 2020, and we can see when the peck occure between months (7,8) and the effect of the virus on this months at 2020.
